## Competitor Visual Patterns (from Transparency Centre)
*Dominant patterns in your space and the gaps worth exploiting.*

*Template for what to log here:*
```
### [CR-0X] [Competitor/space] dominates with [visual pattern] — opportunity gap is [alternative]
Confidence: CONFIRMED | Last updated: YYYY-MM-DD | Evidence: adstransparency.google.com — search "[term]"
Detail: Screenshots saved to visuals/screenshots/YYYY-MM-DD_[term].png
```

---

## What Addy does with this file at session end

After every creative session, ask:
1. Did an image-gen prompt work well or fail badly? → Update or add a CR entry
2. Did Google assign asset labels since last session? → Add format-performance entries
3. Did council veto a copy angle or CTA? → Add a Copy & CTA entry
4. Did Transparency Centre research reveal a clear visual pattern? → Add a competitor entry
5. Did a brand constraint cause a problem (logo, UI crop, colours)? → Add a Brand Constraint entry

If none of the above → write nothing. Only update when evidence actually changes the model.
